parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden stalling of the engine can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries, especially when it occurs at high speeds.
symptoms: the engine shuts off without warning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the oil pump gear can cause engine seizure, leading to costly repairs and potentially dangerous situations, such as stalling in traffic.
symptoms: the oil pump gear walks forward

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Oil leakage can cause a fire hazard, potentially leading to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: oil drips onto the engine or surrounding components
the engine compartment is covered in oil
the vehicle is at risk of catching fire.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Idle Air Control (IAC) module can cause the vehicle to hesitate or stall while accelerating, leading to a loss of power and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates or stalls while accelerating
the engine check light comes on and off
the vehicle loses power while driving at any speed
the vehicle shuts down and comes to a stop.
